Among other things, truth did not serve as a defence under the Criminal and Seditious Libel Law, which also allowed for pre-trial detention. Journalists in Sierra Leone have called it "a watershed moment" or even "Liberation Day". After the signing ceremony at State House, President Bio told BBC Newsday: "You cannot have a vibrant democracy without journalism which is unfettered... of course that poses some problems but that is part of the democratic environment we have to live in."
--BBC-